Creating a simple WebVR chessboard scene with animated cheeses moving randomly at 1 frame per second can be done using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a complete code block that you can use as a web app. This example uses basic HTML5 and CSS for styling, and JavaScript for the animation logic.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Web VR Chessboard with Animated Cheeses</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        #chessboard {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 50px);
            grid-template-rows: repeat(8, 50px);
            position: relative;
        }
        .square {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
        }
        .white {
            background-color: white;
        }
        .black {
            background-color: black;
        }
        .cheese {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            background-color: yellow;
            border-radius: 20px;
            position: absolute;
            transition: transform 0.5s;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="chessboard"></div>
    <script>
        const chessboard = document.getElementById('chessboard');
        const cheeses = [];
        const cheeseCount = 5; // Number of cheeses to animate

        // Create chessboard squares
        for (let row = 0; row < 8; row++) {
            for (let col = 0; col < 8; col++) {
                const square = document.createElement('div');
                square.className = 'square ' + ((row + col) % 2 === 0 ? 'white' : 'black');
                chessboard.appendChild(square);
            }
        }

        // Create cheese elements
        for (let i = 0; i < cheeseCount; i++) {
            const cheese = document.createElement('div');
            cheese.className = 'cheese';
            cheeses.push(cheese);
            chessboard.appendChild(cheese);
        }

        // Function to move cheeses randomly
        function moveCheeses() {
            cheeses.forEach(cheese => {
                const randomRow = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8);
                const randomCol = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8);
                const x = randomCol * 50 + 5; // 5 for centering the cheese
                const y = randomRow * 50 + 5; // 5 for centering the cheese
                cheese.style.transform = `translate(${x}px, ${y}px)`;
            });
        }

        // Move cheeses every second
        setInterval(moveCheeses, 1000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The HTML consists of a `div` for the chessboard, which is populated with squares.
- **CSS Styles**: The CSS styles define the appearance of the chessboard, squares, and cheese pieces. The chessboard is created using CSS Grid.
- **JavaScript Logic**: The JavaScript creates cheese pieces and moves them to random squares on the chessboard every second using `setInterval`.

### How to Use:
1. Copy the entire code block above.
2. Paste it into a new `.html` file (e.g., `chessboard.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser to see the animated cheeses on the chessboard.

This code provides a simple and fun demonstration of a chessboard with animated elements. You can further enhance it by adding more features or styles as needed!
